article.headline: Massachusetts 66, Dayton 47
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. (AP) -- James Life scored 25 points as Massachusetts outscored Dayton by 22 points in the second half to beat the Flyers 66-47 on Saturday. Memphis coach John Calipari, who led the Minutemen to the 1996 Final Four, was a surprise visitor for a halftime ceremony to name the team's home floor the Jack Leaman Court, in honor of the well-liked former coach and broadcaster. Calipari, who took a private plane to the event, left after halftime to coach his team against Tulsa on Saturday night in Memphis. Rashaun Freeman scored 15 of his 19 points and grabbed nine of his 12 rebounds in the second half as the Minutemen (12-13, 7-7 Atlantic 10) outscored the Flyers 40-18 in the second half to overcome a 29-26 halftime deficit. Life, who hit five 3-pointers, also played well defensively, holding Dayton's leading scorer, Brian Roberts, averaging nearly 17 points per game, to nine points on 4-of-10 shooting. Warren Williams led Dayton (13-15, 5-9) with 13 points.
